mer, J.A.|date=1826|issue=v. 1|publisher=Clarendon|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F-mptIYmimAC|page=205}}</ref><ref name="google37">{{cite book|title=A Companion to Latin Studies|publisher=CUP Archive|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=gR09AAAAIAAJ|page=356}}</ref><ref name="google38">{{cite book|title=Peasants, Citizens and Soldiers: Studies in the Demographic History of Roman Italy 225 BC-AD 100|author=de Ligt, L.|date=2012|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-1-107-01318-6|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=G7_CqrKYjnMC|page=236}}</ref><ref name="google39">{{cite book|title=The First Millennium AD in Europe and the Mediterranean: An Archaeological Essay|author=Randsborg, K.|date=1991|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-38787-3|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=sT07AAAAIAAJ|page=93}}</ref><ref name="google40">{{cite book|title=Italy|author1=Facaros, D.|author2=Pauls, M.|date=2004|publisher=Cadogan Guides|isbn=978-1-86011-113-6|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=XixojYgnRtsC|page=11}}</ref> |- |[[Choirokoitia]] |300 – 600 |2,000 | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |<ref>Choirokoitia {{cite web|url=http://www.worldheritagesite.org/sites/choirokoitia.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-04-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140403152522/http://worldheritagesite.org/sites/choirokoitia.html |archivedate=3 April 2014 |df= }}</ref><ref name="google41">{{cite book|title=Cyprus|author=Maric, V.|date=2009|publisher=Lonely Planet Publications|isbn=978-1-74104-803-2|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=6BKlnz-TResC|page=25}}</ref><ref name="google42">{{cite book|title=Travel Cyprus: Illustrated Guide, Greek and Turkish Phrasebooks & Maps (Mobi Travel)|author=MobileReference|date=2011|publisher=MobileReference|isbn=978-1-61198-124-7|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=RpWQKnu97BcC}}</ref><ref name="google43">{{cite book|title=Frommer's Cyprus With Your Family: From the Best Family Beaches to Mountain Villages