es: Dynasty, Religion, and Empire in the North Atlantic|author=Hudson, B.T.|date=2005|publisher=Oxford University Press|isbn=978-0-19-516237-0|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=fH0mL0m95fsC|page=92}}</ref><ref name="google142">{{cite book|title=A Comparative Study of Thirty City-state Cultures: An Investigation|author1=Hansen, M.H.|author2=Københavns universitet. Polis centret|date=2000|issue=v. 21|publisher=Kongelige Danske Videnskabernes Selskab|isbn=9788778761774|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=8qvY8pxVxcwC|page=255}}</ref> |- |[[Edirne]] (Adrianople) | | | | | | | |10,000 | | | | | |28,000 |125,000 |160,000-183,000 |93,000 |100,000 |<ref name="XiGLBQAAQBAJ 2060" /> |- |[[Feodosia]] | | | | | | | | | | | | |40,000 |85,000-88,000 |50,000 |40,000 |36,000-44,000 | |<ref name="XiGLBQAAQBAJ 2060" /> |- |[[Florence]] | | | | | | | | | |15,000 | |50,000-60,000 |80,000-120,000 | |70,000 |70,000 | | |<ref name="auto6">{{cite book|title=The Sovereign State and Its Competitors: An Analysis of Systems Change|author=Spruyt, H.|date=1996|publisher=Princeton University Press|isbn=978-0-691-02910-8|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Jx2Q4hxT5HAC|page=132}}</ref><ref name="auto1" /><ref name="isites.harvard.edu" /><ref name="google135" /><ref name="italyworldclub">{{cite web|url=http://www.italyworldclub.com/toscana/firenze/firenze.htm|title=Firenze, Florence, Tuscany, Italy|publisher=italyworldclub.com|accessdate=2014-09-24}}</ref><ref name="google143">{{cite book|title=Pre-Industrial Cities and Technology|author1=Chant, C.|author2=Goodman, D.|date=2005|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-1-134-63620-4|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=hK-EAgAAQBAJ|page=141}}</ref> |- |[[Genoa]] | | | | | | | | | |80,000 |50,000 | |100,000 |100,000 |60,000 |70,000 |90,000 | |<ref name="auto6" /><ref name="auto1" /><ref name="isites.harvard.edu" /><ref name="google144">{{cite book|title=Before European Hegemony: The World System A.D. 1250–1350|author=Abu-Lughod, J.L.|date=1991|is