{{Infobox Union |name= CNTG |country= [[Guinea]] |affiliation= [[International Trade Union Confederation|ITUC]] |members= |full_name= National Confederation of Guinean Workers |native_name= Confédération Nationale des Travailleurs de Guinée |image= |founded= |current= |head= |dissolved_date= |dissolved_state= |merged_into= |office= [[Conakry]], Guinea |people= [[Rabiatou Serah Diallo]], secretary general |website= |footnotes= }} <!-- Include all unused fields for future use. See [[template talk:Infobox Union]] for usage. -->
The '''National Confederation of Guinean Workers''' (''Confédération Nationale des Travailleurs de Guinée'', CNTG) is a [[national trade union center]] in [[Guinea]]. The CNTG is the largest trade union centre in Guinea, and is affiliated with the [[International Trade Union Confederation]].
[[Ahmed Sékou Touré]], the former president of Guinea, became the leader of the Guinea branch of the French [[Confédération Générale du Travail]] in 1948. The union was renamed to the CNTG in 1956.
