{{unreferenced|date=September 2012}} {{ESC National Year | Year = 1994 | Country = Slovakia | Preselection = Internal Selection | Preselection date = | Entrant = [[Tublatanka]] | Song = [[Nekonečná pieseň]] | Final result = 19th, 15 points | Prev = 1993 | Next = 1996 }} '''Slovakia''' debuted at the '''Eurovision Song Contest 1994''' in [[Dublin]], [[Ireland]].
[[Slovenská televízia|Slovenská Televízia]] (STV), the Slovak public television, selected the Slovak rock band [[Tublatanka]] to represent them for the first time in the history of the Eurovision Song Contest. The song that represented Slovakia was "[[Nekonečná pieseň]]" ("Neverending song"), composed by band member [[Maťo Ďurinda|Martin 'Maťo' Ďurinda]] with lyrics by [[Martin Sarvaš]].
== At Eurovision == Tublatanka performed 15th on the night of the contest, following [[Germany]] and preceding [[Lithuania]]. They received 15 points, placing 19th of 25, relegating Slovakia from the [[Eurovision Song Contest 1995|1995 contest]].
